  stickyNoteInfos:
  - title: 0-1 Line Sequencer
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 5132
      y: -7192
      width: 310
      height: 218
    contents: "Calculating a normalized 0-1 spawnIndex for our particles is often
      very useful as it can be used to sample curves, distribute particles' size,
      position, etc.\n\r\nAs we're spawning 5 particles, the Spawn Index attribute
      will range from 0-4.\r\n\r\nNormalize 0-1 spawnIndex= spawn Index / (Number
      of particles - 1.0) \r\nThis 0-1 value is used in a line sequencer to distribute
      the particles along the line.\r\n"
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: TexIndex
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 6593
      y: -6968
      width: 419
      height: 119
    contents: 'Our U, N, I, T, and Y letters are inside a sprite sheet.

      We''re
      spawning 5 particles and using their spawn index, which ranges from 0 to 4,
      to set our texIndex. By doing so, each particle gets assigned a different letter
      in our Sprite Sheet.

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  - title: 'Offset Animation:'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 4518
      y: -5824
      width: 230
      height: 101
    contents: 'The spawnIndex is used to delay the start of the size and color attribute
      animations.

      This is what makes each letter appear one after the other.

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Unity Font
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 6130
      y: -7949
      width: 456
      height: 107
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Global Spawn EVENT
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 7129
      y: -8727
      width: 840
      height: 107
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Explosion
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 7596
      y: -7977
      width: 456
      height: 107
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: Flipbook Blending
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 11249
      y: -7896
      width: 735
      height: 101
    contents: 
    theme: 
    textSize: Huge
    colorTheme: 2
  - title: 'FlipBook Player:'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 11855
      y: -6584
      width: 221
      height: 153
    contents: 'The Flipbook Player allows you to easily animate your flipbook or
      sprite sheet.

      Just give a frame rate and the block does the rest for
      you.

      In the background, this block is updating the texIndex value to
      animate the frame:

      texIndex +=  frameRate * delta Time ;

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  - title: Blend Frame
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 10777
      y: -6180
      width: 314
      height: 107
    contents: 'This output renders the yellow smoke particle. Each frame is alpha-blended
      with the previous one.

      But with a very low frame rate, we can see steps
      in the animation as we don''t have enough animation frame data. '
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  - title: 'Blend Frame: Motion Vector'
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 12157
      y: -6260
      width: 333
      height: 265
    contents: 'This output is rendering the blue smoke particle. On this output,
      the Motion Vector Blend is activated. This allows us to use another texture
      to blend between frames. In this texture, the pixel displacement from one frame
      to the next is encoded. This allows for smoother interpolation between frames.
      If we look at the edges of our smoke, even at this very low frame rate, the
      interpolation stays smooth.





      The motion vector texture doesn''t need
      to be huge, and can help reduce the number of frames in a flipbook animation.

'
    theme: 
    textSize: Small
    colorTheme: 3
  categories: []
  uiBounds:
    serializedVersion: 2
    x: 4493
    y: -8727
    width: 8022
    height: 4194
